Citation.sAbstract: In this work, densities q, speeds of sound u, and viscosities g, have been measured over the whole  composition range for the binary mixtures of diethylene glycol monomethyl ether (DEGMME),  CH3(OCH2CH2)2OH with 1-hexanol, CH3(CH2)5OH, 1-octanol, CH3(CH2)7OH, and 1-decanol, CH3(CH2)9OH  at T = (293.15, 298.15, 303.15, and 308.15) K along with the properties of the pure components. By using  the experimental values of q, u, and g, excess molar volume, VE  m, deviations in viscosity, Dg, isentropic  compressibility jS, deviations in isentropic compressibility DjS, deviations of the speed of sound Du,  have been calculated. The viscosity results have also been analysed in terms of some semi-empirical  equations.
Citation.sTitle: Volumetric, acoustic, and viscometric studies of molecular interactions in binary mixtures of diethylene glycol monomethyl ether with 1-alkanols at temperatures from (293.15 to 308.15) K
